entry.title: [perf] Don't use IsOutOfFlowPositioned in LayoutObject::StyleDidChange
entry.content:
The positioned_state_ is cleared within LayoutObject::StyleWillChange

and set within LayoutBoxModelObject::StyleDidChange (but after

LayoutObject::StyleDidChange). IsOutOfFlowPositioned hence will return

false.



This resulted us in using "full" layout when we intended it to be

"simplified". Use the style as the source of truth instead.

entry.title: [@scope] Let :scope match shadow hosts
entry.content:
This CL makes it possible once again to @scope again the shadow host.

Fixing this requires several changes:



- The internal :true pseudo-class must be allowed to match

the host (the change in SelectorChecker::CheckOne).

This pseudo-class is prepended to any compound selector

that contains :scope.

- Observing the kScopeActivation relation must not count

as exceeding the scope (the change in SelectorChecker::

MatchSelector).

- When matching rules for the shadow host, we must collect rules

from the universal bucket when :scope may be present.

entry.title: blink/public: Split WebPrivatePtr in GCed and RefCounted pointer
entry.content:
Split the implementation of WebPrivatePtr into WebPrivatePtrForGC and

WebPrivatePtrForRefcounted.



WebPrivatePtrForRefCounted: Same as WebPrivatePtr for

base::scoped_refptr only. Still requires using untyped storage as the

destruction behavior should avoid executing destructors of the

ref-counted types.



WebPrivatePtrForGC: Can directly use the Blink handle as ctor/dtor are

safe to be used with forward declared types and no destructors are

invoked. Using the handle directly has the benefits:

a. PersistentLocation is now available for all such references, making

it much easier to find leaks for debugging.

b. The GC plugin can find (see ignore annotation) roots that are

introduced on the managed object graph. This is a source of leaks and

bloat.



Undo the restrictions from https://crrev.com/c/4637546. Constructors

may now be defined in header files again. This simplifies the usage of

the pointers.

entry.title: Exo: Translate host window bounds with device scale factor.
entry.content:
This CL lets UpdateSurfaceBounds update host window bounds with

device scale factor.

GetScale() is a scale of surface tree relative to surface while host

window is transformed by device scale factor if client sends surface

in pixel coordinates.

Therefore, we must transform into device scale factor in such case.



ClientControlledShellSurface is not affected by this change as

`client_submits_surfaces_in_pixel_coordinates_` may only be enabled

on Lacros client.



This CL does not affect the behavior immediately unless clip

delegation is enabled by removing `quad_within_window` flag inside

OverlayCandidateFactory. Without this flag, root_surface_origin() is

always zero so that no offset is added.

entry.title: Introduce LRUCache for SharedDictionaryStorage
entry.content:
Currently, a SharedDictionaryStorage is kept alive as long as there is a

CorsURLLoaderFactory object that matches its

SharedDictionaryIsolationKey. This means that once CorsURLLoaderFactory

is deleted, Chromium needs to load the metadata from the database again.

For example, if a site has a cross origin iframe in every pages, a page

navigation in the site always triggers the database read for the cross

origin iframe. This is not good for performance.



To mitigate this problem, this CL introduces a LRUCache in

SharedDictionaryManager to keep SharedDictionaryStorages. The cached

SharedDictionaryStorage will be evicted when MemoryPressure is detected.



Bug: 1413922

entry.title: Revert "webauthn: group AuthenticatorCommonImpl's request-specific state"
entry.content:
This reverts commit 72a85e64b289f68b26a7376232e01c22eec965e5.



Reason for revert:



https://ci.chromium.org/ui/p/chromium/builders/luci.chromium.ci/Mac10.15%20Tests is consistently failing external/wpt/webauthn/getcredential-abort.https.html starting with build



https://ci.chromium.org/ui/p/chromium/builders/ci/Mac10.15%20Tests/39634/blamelist



This is the only CL in the blamelist touching webauthn.



Original change's description:

> webauthn: group AuthenticatorCommonImpl's request-specific state

>

> I made a mistake in 63aece93df and didn't clear the experiment state in

> `Cleanup`. But that's too easy a mistake to make, so this change fixes

> it by grouping all request-specific state into a struct and resetting

> the whole struct for each request. This way, it'll be much harder to

> make a similar error in the future.

>

> Bug: 1456525

> Change-Id: I0045c00c88d7a13aa74ce8e680950cd77b3903e5

> Reviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/4661916
